  "texts": [
    "This approach also involves transforming CFG into CFT and utilizing polyhedra-based abstract interpretation to infer input conditionals.",
    "The resulting symbolic WCET formula is simplified and embedded for real-time evaluation.",
    "Evaluations using TACLeBench benchmarks [44] highlight the method's effectiveness in reflecting how procedure arguments influence WCET, facilitating adaptive scheduling.",
    "Implemented as an extension to the OTAWA WCET analysis tool, this method has been validated on various real-time benchmarks, offering advancements in adaptive scheduling.Building on the advancements in WCET analysis, Dharishini et al. [47] present a static analyzer designed to compute WCET for multithreaded programs using Hoare's Communicating Sequential Processes (CSP) [48].",
    "This approach transforms multithreaded programs into CSP specifications, allowing the identification of concurrent regions and partial orders among threads."
